{
  "texts": [
    "24For the odd w case, we take r ∈ Z + 1/2 and the state [|Φ w ⟩] σ w satisfiesF ± r [|Φ w ⟩] σ w = [F ± r±w/2 |Φ w ⟩] σ w = 0, for all r ≥ 1/2.This implies the OPEF ± (z) V w m 1,m 2 (x i; z i) = O(1).",
    "This is precisely the behaviour of F ± with the vertex operator V w m 1,m 2 of (3.10).",
    "Therefore, in the case of odd w, we have the relationship between states and operators asV w m 1,m 2 (x; z) ↔ [|Φ w ⟩] σ w, (3.11)where m 1 and m 2 satisfy the constraints in (3.4).",
    "Unfortunately, the even w case is not quite as simple.",
    "Consider r ∈ Z, such that the states [|Φ ± w ⟩] σ w satisfyF + r [|Φ + w ⟩] σ w = [F + r+w/2 |Φ + w ⟩] σ w = 0, for all r ≥ 0, F - r [|Φ + w ⟩] σ w = [F - r-w/2 |Φ + w ⟩] σ w = 0, for all r ≥ 1, F + r [|Φ - w ⟩] σ w = [F + r+w/2 |Φ - w ⟩] σ w = 0, for all r ≥ 1, F - r [|Φ - w ⟩] σ w = [F - r-w/2 |Φ - w ⟩] σ w = 0, for all r ≥ 0."
  ]
}